This paper deals with opinion mining, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques such as Conditional Random Fields (CRF) and semi-supervised pattern recognition, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the likely sub-categories for this paper.
